The system is protected from major releases by internal excess flow valves, check valves, relief valves, manual shut-off valves, and emergency shut-off valves. The loadout risers used in filling nurse tanks are protected by breakaway couplers designed to immediately stop the flow of ammonia if the line or a hose breaks. All of the main storage tank valves are locked when not in use.

Since this facility is located in relatively close proximity to the Town of Low Moor, provisions have been designed to notify all affected persons in Low Moor. An evacuation plan is in place.

In the event of a serious release, the following steps will be taken:

1. Remain calm, accurately assess the situation, exercise extreme caution, and proceed in a well thought out, systematic manner to resolve the emergency situation;
2. Notify local authorities via a 911 call;
3. Notify the National Response Center;
4. Isolate the area;
5. Remove injured personnel, if it is safe to attempt to do so;
6. Evacuate the immediate area;
7. Assist emergency responders when they arrive at the scene; and,
8. Notify state agencies.

